==Trivia==
*In the comics, Aldrich Killian was one of the scientists who developed the [[Extremis]] virus, selling it to a terrorist group and committing suicide out of guilt later on.
**The movie version is an amalgamation of his character, '''Mallen''', and the modern version of Mandarin.

==Behind the Scenes==
*[[Kevin Feige]] revealed in an interview that early drafts of ''[[Iron Man (film)|Iron Man]]'' depicted the [[Mandarin]] as a younger individual (a contemporary to [[Tony Stark]]) who would have business dealings with [[Stark Industries]]. Though this idea was eventually omitted to further push [[Obadiah Stane]] as the main antagonist of the film as opposed to the Mandarin, some of the traits for the character were incorporated into Aldrich Killian in ''[[Iron Man 3]]''.
*Before [[Guy Pearce]] was cast as Aldrich Killian, {{WPS|Nikolaj Coster-Waldau}} and [[Jude Law]] were considered for the role.
*The movie's depiction of Killian was initially described by [[Shane Black]] as the [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]]'s version of the Mandarin, but the release of ''[[All Hail the King]]'' has proven otherwise. However, in 2016, Black confirmed in an interview with {{WPS|Uproxx}} that ''All Hail the King'' was made as an apology to fans who were angry about the Mandarin twist.
*[[Chris Brewster]] was a stunt double for [[Guy Pearce]] in the role of Aldrich Killian.

